Share with:
Human Resource Manager Job (Manufacturing Industrial Equipment), Tangerang, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Human Resources
Industry:
Manufacturing
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
06 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is currently recruiting on behalf of a leading company with a core focus on manufacturing custom-made mechanical components and cutting tools. As an established company serving a broad range of industries such as automotive, aerospace, heavy industry, food and beverage, pharmacy, medical, sanitary products, etc. As expansion continues, our client is seeking a qualified candidate for the job of Human Resources (HR) Manager, to be based in Tangerang, Indonesia.
Key job responsibilities:
Build/Establish the human capital capabilities to support our expansion plans in Indonesia.
Formulate and implement HR strategies and policies which support business directions and achieve business objectives, covering: Compensation and Benefits; Recruitment; Training and Development; Talent Development and Succession Planning; Organizational Development; Employee Engagement
Lead and manage the HR professionals based on their functions in providing effective and efficient HR support.
Act as organization change agent and internal consultant to Business Heads on all human capital issues.
Provide advisory inputs to Director on all human capital issues.
Work closely with management to support the implementation of company’s policy and initiatives.
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in Human Resources Management or any related background from reputably university
At least 6 years at the managerial level, preferrably from Automotive/Manufacturing background
Sound knowledge of employment laws and HR practices in Indonesia
Competent in all HR functional areas (staffing, compensation, learning and development, change management etc).
Strong leadership and conceptual abilities
Result oriented, self-starter with initiative and strong execution drive
Strong communication and interpersonal skills
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.